<div>
<p class="ecxMsoNormal">Speaking during an operation to drive out thousands of livestock from Tsavo West Monday, Kenya Wildlife Service (KWS) warden in-charge of the park Rose Malenya called for "a collaborative approach among stakeholders" in the fight against illegal grazing in the reserve.</p>

</div>
<div>
<p class="ecxMsoNormal">During the operation, more than 20 herdsmen were arrested and 11,000 livestock driven out of the park.</p>
